ng to add the old dependency would cause import failures. The generator generates a schema that expects tools.jackson.databind.node.ObjectNode, which aligns with the v5 API. However, using tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode doesn’t work for com.fasterxml.JsonNode due to type incompatibility. This means that adding the old dependency isn't just unnecessary; it could cause confusion. I also need to check if the swagger-annotations version 2.2.25 is still acceptable within the parent POM's dependency management.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_B2FB95uKh2qty0pzBQoFsvdT|fc_00e9477d9181f574016a40641a45208197b70db6736f84eb0d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request,re\nurl='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/github/victools/jsonschema-generator-parent/5.0.0/jsonschema-generator-parent-5.0.0.pom'\ntext=urllib.request.urlopen(url,timeout=20).read().decode()\nfor pat in ['tools.jackson','swagger-annotations','classmate','maven.compiler.release']:\n print('\\n---',pat,'---')\n idx=text.find(pat)\n print(text[max(0,idx-1000):idx+2000] if idx!=-1 else 'not found')\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6900, "output": 675, "cacheRead": 16896, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24471, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782604812513, "responseId": "resp_00e9477d9181f574016a40640d17f48197bbc36d741b75b1ed"}}
