[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating migration requirements**\n\nI'm noticing that v5 migrates from com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode to tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode, and I’m wondering if that requires a more deterministic setup. The usual scaffold might include the library and possibly transitive tools.jackson, but tests might need to reference tools.jackson instead. \n\nThere's a compile issue because of the missing com.fasterxml, so I need to decide whether to add jackson-databind to keep old imports. The user indicated the setup might involve dependencies or environmental properties.\n\n**Analyzing artifact dependencies**\n\nFor the module artifact POM, jsonschema-generator and swagger-annotations are included, meaning both need to be added when using the module. The existing build already adds them, but I wonder if the generated scaffold focuses solely on the target library? The deterministic setup might require adding dependencies ahead of generation. \n\nIt seems the current build fails due to an issue where it can't find the class com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode. Fixing the import and types in the test code instead of adding new dependencies could also be a solution.\n\n**Assessing compatibility issues**\n\nI see that trying to add the old dependency would cause import failures. The generator generates a schema that expects tools.jackson.databind.node.ObjectNode, which aligns with the v5 API. However, using tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode doesn’t work for com.fasterxml.JsonNode due to type incompatibility. This means that adding the old dependency isn't just unnecessary; it could cause confusion. I also need to check if the swagger-annotations version 2.2.25 is still acceptable within the parent POM's dependency management.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00e9477d9181f574016a40640e3780819787d268c04269b318\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypte